  ==============================================================================
    RPCE Webservices (deprecated)
  ==============================================================================
  -->

  <!--
    The RPCE webservices subsystem uses a finite set of namespaces - something is either in the api, entity, fault, or enumeration namespace.
    This quite often leads to conflicts/overwriting of classes in that namespace.  This prevents you from having duplicate
    RPCE webservice class names.  But for referenced classes this is not an issue unless you call these RPCE webservices via
    soap.local, or generate the clients clients in the same directory. So to turn off the warning in studio change this to true.
  -->

  <param name="AllowSoapWebServiceReferenceNamespaceCollisions" value="false"/>

  <!--
    The RPCE webservices bundle was set to ignore bean version conflicts, several people have pointed out that this
    is quite dangerous. So we have changed the default behavior, and added an annotation to get back to that behavior,
    however we do not want to disrupt current customers in a minor version upgrade so the new behavior is dependent
    on setting this to true.
   -->
  <param name="UseSafeBundleForWebServiceOperations" value="true"/>

  <!-- The RPCE webservices have to initialize the definition and create the service objects.
    If true this will cause the creation of the service objects at startup of the RPCE webservice servlet, it does
    this by creating a thread and that thread will wait until the application servlet is started and will then
    start the RPCE webservices.  This can be overridden on a per node basis if only some nodes respond to RPCE requests.
  -->
  <param name="LoadSoapServicesOnStartup" value="false"/>

